About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Nice appearance, good value, light weight and seems durable. Gift for my sister. Great size for a carry-on luggage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and sturdy
reviews.reviewText: Great quality. I even rode on this suitcase and I use it every day, packed full of work stuff, and it's still going strong after several months of tough use.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I was looking for!
reviews.reviewText: Loved that it was light. Beautiful and Just what I was looking for.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: For the price of this carry on luggage it’s well made . We just came back from vacation and it worked as it should with no problems at all.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice suitcase. Served the purpose.
reviews.reviewText: Not super heavy duty and pretty small. With that said I was able to pack a lot of stuff in there for my two day trip. Probably could have packed for a few more days it has great organization with nifty compartments. Value worth the money in my opinion.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2015
reviews.reviewText: So far so good. There are pros and cons. I would say for the price it is a good choice.Pros:It looks as pictured and is very sturdy, and spacious. 360 degree rotation. Moves smoothly.Cons:There are two issues: 1. The zip inside broke after two travels. It is still holding there that if you zip it very carefully it can still be closed. 2. If you put too much comparatively heavy stuff on the pull handle side, you won't be able to pull out the handle all the way because it is stuck.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice carry on bag
reviews.reviewText: I like having a bag that is easy to spot when in a sea of other bags. I like hard sided luggage and it seems to be more protective to the contents. This bag is a bit smaller than my last carry on but I have noticed that carry on requirements are getting smaller and many airlines are being much more vigilant about checking. I have used it a couple of times and have actually had to check it due to overcrowding in the overhead storage. It has got a few scrapes already but to significant damage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It’s cute, and as described. The clear protective can be pulled off and was not an issue. This is my first “hard shell” tho it is soft plastic. I worried about checking it, but it came through fine 6 times now. The lock only lasted 1 trip before it jammed. Twist-ties work great! Wheels are good. The bag is great for a weekend. Packing for longer than 3 days was tough and I needed an additional carry on for tennis shoes and toiletries. The bad is these shells do not have outside pockets like a soft case and I missed those pockets for chargers, books, boarding pass, etc.

reviews.reviewText: Sturdy & Light weight cabin trolly case. It looks small but you can get a lot inside it. Brilliant for Ryan Air flights, as perfect size.
